y's term, "reconstructed"-individualism is not merely compatible with but necessary to democratic community. Conceiving selfhood and community as interrelated processes, they call for an ongoing reform of social conditions so as to educate and liberate individuality, and, conversely, they affirm the essential role individuality plays in vitalizing communal efforts at reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aIndividualism in literature. 0aIndividualismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aLiterature and societyzUnited States. 0aPhilosophy, Americany19th century. 0aPhilosophy, Americany20th century. 0aPragmatism in literature. 4aDemocracy. 4aEthics. 4aIndividualism. 4aJohn Dewey. 4aPragmatism. 4aRalph Ellison. 4aRalph Waldo Emerson. 4aTranscendentalism. 4aWilliam James. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Pragmatism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311070729840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823242122zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823242122423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823242122.jpg  a978-3-11-070729-8  FUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK